## 🐛 Bug Report

When reading a .xlsx file like the attachment, exceljs throws an error: Invalid row number in model at Row.set model.

Lib version: 4.3.0

## Steps To Reproduce

Here is a example file to reproduce the situation. [attachment](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/files/6464604/staged_data.xlsx)

```javascript
const workbookHelper = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
const cache = [];
workbookHelper.xlsx
  .readFile(`${__dirname}/staged_data.xlsx`)
  .then((workbook) => {
    fs.outputFile(
      `${__dirname}/__excel__/src.json`,
      JSON.stringify(workbook, function (key, value) {
        if (typeof value === 'object' && value !== null) {
          if (cache.indexOf(value) !== -1) {
            return;
          }
          cache.push(value);
        }
        return value;
      })
    );

    const spreadJSON = transform2SpreadJSON(workbook);
    fs.outputFile(
      `${__dirname}/__excel__/res.json`,
      JSON.stringify(spreadJSON)
    );
  });
```

## The expected behaviour:
Get the correct result json file without any error.
